                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18181028-133-victim932 t18181028-133-viclabel758"></join>, and lives in <placeName id="t18181028-133-crimeloc759">East-street, Manchester-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18181028-133-crimeloc759" type="placeName" value="East-street, Manchester-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18181028-133-crimeloc759" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18181028-133-off756 t18181028-133-crimeloc759"></join>. On the 19th of October we lost the copper, which was fixed in the wash-house.</p>
               <p>RICHARD COATES. I am a constable. On the 19th of October, about seven o'clock in the evening, I stopped the prisoner in Marylebone-lane, with the copper on his head. I asked him where he got it; he said a man gave him half a crown to carry it to Berners-street - the man was a stranger. I told him he was going the wrong way to Berners-street - I secured him. He said he did not take it; but he never would tell who the man was that did.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. It was given to me to carry.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18181028-133-verdict760" type="verdictDescription">
